(Linux setup)
We use a patched version of kivy on the BTP machines.
For you development system you can do the following:
(This is my setup)
I just grap the installed kivy package from /usr/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/kivy
and place it in my home dir and name it kivy-btp.
I then replace kivy-btp/data/images/defaulttheme.atlas and defaulttheme-0.png with the ones
from this directory.
I also replace kivy-btp/data/style.py

Then I make a symlink from within the childsplay tree:
cd ~/GIT/childsplay
ln -s ../../kivy-btp kivy

Done, now childsplay will use the kivy from the homedirectory.
